rdnPacketCableGroup.name: rdnPacketCableGroup

revisions.description: Added Differentiated Services Code Point(DSCP) to Motorola PacketCable. Added rdnPktDQoSDscp, rdnPktMMDscp, rdnPktEMDscp and rdnPktESCccDscp.
Fixed this MIB MODULE'S description and its revison history. Added Copyright Statement into MIB modules's description.
Added RKS trap support to Motorola PacketCable. Added rdnPktEMRKSFailureTrapEnable.
Corrected the comments for rdnPktDQoSEmergencyPreemptTrap mib object.
Add Preemption mib object to Motorola PacketCable.

Changed MAX-ACCESS of the following objects from read-only to not-accessible: rdnGateId, rdnGateDirection, rdnPktDQosCopsHandle. Removed object rdnGateID and replaced with rdnGateId. Value of rdnGateDirection downstream(2) added.

BcidDataArray.name: BcidDataArray
BcidDataArray.description: An array holds the Billing Correlation ID.

rdnPktDQoSCOPSStatus.name: rdnPktDQoSCOPSStatus
rdnPktDQoSCOPSStatus.description: This object is used to enable/disable PacketCable DQoS feature. When this object is set to FALSE(2), DQoS will be disabled.

rdnPktDQoSCMTSIp.name: rdnPktDQoSCMTSIp
rdnPktDQoSCMTSIp.description: An IP address can be configured for the CMTS. If that IP address is configured, BSR will only accept a COPS connection destined to that IP address. Example, loop back, HFC or network IP address.

rdnPktDQoSPEPID.name: rdnPktDQoSPEPID
rdnPktDQoSPEPID.description: An ASCII string to identify the CMTS. Default - Motorola CMTS.

rdnPktDQoSClientAccpTimer.name: rdnPktDQoSClientAccpTimer
rdnPktDQoSClientAccpTimer.description: This object specifies the Time that limits the CMTS to wait for the Client Accept from the CMS/GC in milliseconds.

rdnPktDQoST0Timer.name: rdnPktDQoST0Timer
rdnPktDQoST0Timer.description: This object specifies the period of time in seconds that a Gate may be allocated without being authorized.

rdnPktDQoST1Timer.name: rdnPktDQoST1Timer
rdnPktDQoST1Timer.description: This object specifies the time in seconds that may elapse between the authorization and commit. This provisioned value is only used if the T1 value is not provided by the GC/CMS.

rdnPktDQoSCopsTrapEnable.name: rdnPktDQoSCopsTrapEnable
rdnPktDQoSCopsTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether the PacketCable COPS connection trap should be generated. If its value is set to enabled(1), then traps are generated. If the value is disabled(2), then traps are not generated. By default, this object has the value disabled(2).

rdnPktDQoSResReqTrapEnable.name: rdnPktDQoSResReqTrapEnable
rdnPktDQoSResReqTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether the PacketCable Resource Request trap should be generated. If its value is set to enabled(1), then traps are generated. If the value is disabled(2), then traps are not generated. By default, this object has the value disabled(2).

rdnPktESTrapEnable.name: rdnPktESTrapEnable
rdnPktESTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether the PacketCable ES status trap should be generated. If its value is set to enabled(1), then traps are generated. If the value is disabled(2), then traps are not generated. By default, this object has the value disabled(2).

rdnPktESEnable.name: rdnPktESEnable
rdnPktESEnable.description: Indicates whether the PacketCable ES feature is enabled. If its value is set to enabled(1), then Packet Cable ES functionality will operate based on the information received in the Gate-Set message from the CMS. If the value is disabled(2), then the Packet Cable ES functionality will not function according to the information received in the Gate-Set message from the CMS. By default, this object has the value enabled(1).

rdnPktDQoSEmergencyTrapEnable.name: rdnPktDQoSEmergencyTrapEnable
rdnPktDQoSEmergencyTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether the PacketCable Emergency Call trap should be generated. If its value is set to enabled(1), then traps are generated. If the value is disabled(2), then traps are not generated. By default, this object has the value disabled(2).

rdnPktDQoSEmergencyPreemption.name: rdnPktDQoSEmergencyPreemption
rdnPktDQoSEmergencyPreemption.description: Indicates whether the PacketCable Emergency Preemption is disabled or set to a specific option of dropping a normal dqos voice call. If its value is set to most-recent(1), the most-recent normal dqos voice call of that Service Class is dropped when the bandwidth of the Emergency Service Class has maxed out. The Preemption can only occur if that Service Class has 'allowShared' turned on. Otherwise, Preemption can not occur and thus, the high priority call can not be completed. If the value is oldest(2), the oldest normal dqos voice call is dropped. If the value is random, random normal dqos voice call is dropped. By default, this object has the value disabled(0).

rdnPktEMRKSFailureTrapEnable.name: rdnPktEMRKSFailureTrapEnable
rdnPktEMRKSFailureTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether the PacketCable EM RKS Failure trap should be generated. If its value is set to enabled(1), then the trap is generated. If the value is disabled(2), then the trap is not generated. By default, this object has the value disabled(2).

rdnPktDQoSDscp.name: rdnPktDQoSDscp
rdnPktDQoSDscp.description: The contents of the Differentiated Services Code Point(DSCP) for DQoS. DSCP is intended to supersede the existing definitions of the IPv4 TOS octet and the IPv6 Traffic Class octet. By setting this value, DSCP will apply to all the DQoS traffic IP header.

rdnPktMMDscp.name: rdnPktMMDscp
rdnPktMMDscp.description: The contents of the Differentiated Services Code Point(DSCP) for Multimedia. DSCP is intended to supersede the exsiting definitions of the IPv4 TOS octet and the IPv6 Traffic Class octet. By setting this value, DSCP will apply to all the Multimedia traffic IP header.

rdnPktEMDscp.name: rdnPktEMDscp
rdnPktEMDscp.description: The contents of the Differentiated Services Code Point(DSCP) for Event Message and Electronic Surveillance Call Data Connection(CDC). DSCP is intended to supersede the existing definitions of the IPv4 TOS octet and the IPv6 Traffic Class octet. By setting this value, DSCP will apply to all the Event Message traffic IP header and Electronic Surveillance Call Data Connection traffic IP header.

rdnPktESCccDscp.name: rdnPktESCccDscp
rdnPktESCccDscp.description: The contents of the Differentiated Services Code Point(DSCP) for Electronic Surveillance Call Content Connection(CCC). DSCP is intended to supersede the existing definitions of the IPv4 TOS octet and the IPv6 Traffic Class octet. By setting this value, DSCP will apply to all the Electronic Surveillance Call Content Connection traffic IP header.

rdnGateStatsTable.name: rdnGateStatsTable
rdnGateStatsTable.description: This table provide PacketCable statistics of DQoS gate.

rdnGateStatsEntry.name: rdnGateStatsEntry
rdnGateStatsEntry.description: Each entry provides a set of statistics objects for DQoS gate.

rdnGateId.name: rdnGateId
rdnGateId.description: This attribute is the identifier for allocated gate.

rdnGateStatsState.name: rdnGateStatsState
rdnGateStatsState.description: This attribute describes current state Idle(0), Start(1), Allocated(2), Authorized(3), Reserved(4), RemoteCommitted(5), LocalCommitted(6), Committed(7).

rdnGateStatsSubscriberIP.name: rdnGateStatsSubscriberIP
rdnGateStatsSubscriberIP.description: This attribute describes the IP address of MTA requesting the gate. Issue:(IPV4 ONLY)

rdnGateStatsRKSPrimaryAddr.name: rdnGateStatsRKSPrimaryAddr
rdnGateStatsRKSPrimaryAddr.description: This attribute describes Primary Record Keeping Server's IP address, the record keeper to whom event records are sent.

rdnGateStatsRKSPrimaryPort.name: rdnGateStatsRKSPrimaryPort
rdnGateStatsRKSPrimaryPort.description: This attribute describes Primary Record Keeping Server Port, the port number for event records to be sent.

rdnGateStatsRKSSecondaryAddr.name: rdnGateStatsRKSSecondaryAddr
rdnGateStatsRKSSecondaryAddr.description: This attribute describes Secondary Record Keeping Server's IP address, the record keeper to whom event records are sent.

rdnGateStatsRKSSecondaryPort.name: rdnGateStatsRKSSecondaryPort
rdnGateStatsRKSSecondaryPort.description: This attribute describes Secondary Record Keeping Server Port, the port number for event records to be sent.

rdnGateStatsEventFlag.name: rdnGateStatsEventFlag
rdnGateStatsEventFlag.description: 0x01 - Batch Processing. If set the CMTS MUST accumulate event records as part of a batch file and send to the Record Keeping Server at periodic intervals. If clear the CMTS MUST send the event records to the Record Keeping Serverin real-time.

rdnGateStatsBillingCorrelationID.name: rdnGateStatsBillingCorrelationID
rdnGateStatsBillingCorrelationID.description: This attribute is the identifier assigned by the CMS for all records related to the session.

rdnGateStatsDurationTime.name: rdnGateStatsDurationTime
rdnGateStatsDurationTime.description: This attribute describes the time that gate was commited.

rdnGateStatsSlotNum.name: rdnGateStatsSlotNum
rdnGateStatsSlotNum.description: This attribute describes the CMTS slot number.

rdnGateStatsUpSfid.name: rdnGateStatsUpSfid
rdnGateStatsUpSfid.description: This attribute describes the upstream SFID.

rdnGateStatsDnSfid.name: rdnGateStatsDnSfid
rdnGateStatsDnSfid.description: This attribute describes the downstream SFID.

rdnGateStatsResourceID.name: rdnGateStatsResourceID
rdnGateStatsResourceID.description: This attribute is an RSVP object that's used as an identifier for future resource changes.

rdnGateStatsESCDCAddr.name: rdnGateStatsESCDCAddr
rdnGateStatsESCDCAddr.description: This attribute describes the DF's IP address, the DF to whom duplicated event messages are sent.

rdnGateStatsESCDCPort.name: rdnGateStatsESCDCPort
rdnGateStatsESCDCPort.description: This attribute describes the DF's Port for CDC, the port number for duplicated event messages to be sent.

rdnGateStatsESFlag.name: rdnGateStatsESFlag
rdnGateStatsESFlag.description: If bit 0 is set - DUP-Event. If set the CMTS MUST send a duplicate copy of all event messages relate to this gate to the DF-IP-Address for CDC (rdnGateStatsESCDCAddr). If bit 1 is set the CMTS MUST send a duplicate copy of all packets matching the classifier(s) fo this gate to the DF-IP-Address-for-CCC (rdnGateStatsESCCCAddr).

rdnGateStatsESCCCAddr.name: rdnGateStatsESCCCAddr
rdnGateStatsESCCCAddr.description: This attribute describes the DF's IP address for CCC, the DF to whom duplicated classifier matched packets are sent.

rdnGateStatsESCCCPort.name: rdnGateStatsESCCCPort
rdnGateStatsESCCCPort.description: This attribute describes the DF's Port for CCC, the port number for duplicated classifier matched packets to be sent.

rdnGateStatsESCCCId.name: rdnGateStatsESCCCId
rdnGateStatsESCCCId.description: An Identifier used to identify the intercept order to the Law Enforcement Agency.

rdnGateSpecTable.name: rdnGateSpecTable
rdnGateSpecTable.description: This table contains DQoS Gate Specification statistics of upstream and downstream.

rdnGateSpecEntry.name: rdnGateSpecEntry
rdnGateSpecEntry.description: Each entry contain DQoS Gate Specification statistics of the upstream or downstream.

rdnGateDirection.name: rdnGateDirection
rdnGateDirection.description: This attribute describes the direction of the gate specification.

rdnGateSpecProtocol.name: rdnGateSpecProtocol
rdnGateSpecProtocol.description: This attribute describes the Protocol to match in the IP header.

rdnGateSpecSourceIP.name: rdnGateSpecSourceIP
rdnGateSpecSourceIP.description: This attribute describes the source IP V4 address, zero for no match.

rdnGateSpecSourcePort.name: rdnGateSpecSourcePort
rdnGateSpecSourcePort.description: This attribute describes source port. Zero for no match.

rdnGateSpecDestIP.name: rdnGateSpecDestIP
rdnGateSpecDestIP.description: This attribute describes the destination IP V4 address, zero for no match.

rdnGateSpecDestPort.name: rdnGateSpecDestPort
rdnGateSpecDestPort.description: This attribute describes destination port. Zero for no match.

rdnGateSpecServiceFlowID.name: rdnGateSpecServiceFlowID
rdnGateSpecServiceFlowID.description: This attribute describes the service flow ID that maps to the Gate. This value could be zero if a Gate is viewed prior to a SFID being assigned to the Gate.

rdnGateSpecFlags.name: rdnGateSpecFlags
rdnGateSpecFlags.description: autoCommit(1), resources Commit immediately upon reservation. commitNotAllowed(2), CMTS ignores any COMMIT messages for the gate.

rdnGateSpecSessionClass.name: rdnGateSpecSessionClass
rdnGateSpecSessionClass.description: This attribute identifies the proper admission control policy or parameters to be applied for the gate. unspecified (255), normalPriority (1), highPriority (2).

rdnGateSpecDiffServCode.name: rdnGateSpecDiffServCode
rdnGateSpecDiffServCode.description: This attribute describes Differentiated Services Code Point.

rdnGateSpecT1Timer.name: rdnGateSpecT1Timer
rdnGateSpecT1Timer.description: This attribute describes Gate Transition timer in seconds, the time limit between authorization and a commit.

rdnGateSpecTokenBuckRate.name: rdnGateSpecTokenBuckRate
rdnGateSpecTokenBuckRate.description: Token Bucket Rate, (r) 32 bit IEEE floating point number used in Bandwidth Calculations. Specifies the token bucket that the traffic conforms to. Part of TSpec.

rdnGateSpecBuckSize.name: rdnGateSpecBuckSize
rdnGateSpecBuckSize.description: Token Bucket Size (b) 32 bit IEEE floating point number used in Bandwidth Calculations. Specifies the token bucket that the traffic conforms ot. Part of TSpec.

rdnGateSpecPeakDataRate.name: rdnGateSpecPeakDataRate
rdnGateSpecPeakDataRate.description: Peak Data Rate (p) 32 bit IEEE floating point number used in Bandwidth Calculations. Specifies the Peak Data Rate at which the source sends traffic. Part of TSpec.

rdnGateSpecMinPoliceUnit.name: rdnGateSpecMinPoliceUnit
rdnGateSpecMinPoliceUnit.description: Minimum Policed Unit (m) 32 bit integer. The smallest packet size that the source generates, if asmaller packet is sent, it will count as a packet of size m for the purpose fo policing. Part of TSpec.

rdnGateSpecMaxPacketSize.name: rdnGateSpecMaxPacketSize
rdnGateSpecMaxPacketSize.description: Maximum Packet Size (M) 32 bit integer. Maximum packet size (including IP and higher layer headers) that are generated by the source. Part of TSpec.

rdnGateSpecReserveRate.name: rdnGateSpecReserveRate
rdnGateSpecReserveRate.description: Rate (R) 32 bit IEEE floating point integer. The amount of bandwidth allocated to the flow. Must be greater than or equal to (r) from the TSpec. Part of RSpec.

rdnGateSlackTerm.name: rdnGateSlackTerm
rdnGateSlackTerm.description: Slack Term (S) 32 bit integer. Delay Bound part of RSpec.

rdnPktDQoSCopsReason.name: rdnPktDQoSCopsReason
rdnPktDQoSCopsReason.description: This entry contains the rdnPktDQoSCopsTrap reason code 1 = The CMTS COPS connection to the CMS/GC is established. specified in the rdnPktDQoSCopsCmsIpAddr field. 2 = Can't establish the COPS connection with the IP address specified in the rdnPktDQoSCopsCmsIpAddr field. 3 = The CMS attempting to make the COPS connection is not authorized to make the connection. The IP address is specified in the rdnPktDQoSCopsCmsIpAddr field. 4 = The CMTS COPS connection to the CMS/GC is closed. The CMTS has received a ClientClose from the CMS/GC. The IP address of the CMS/GC is specified in the rdnPktDQoSCopsCmsIpAddr field. 5 = The CMTS COPS connection to the CMS/GC is disconnected. The connection was administratively closed via a command from the console of the CMTS. The IP address of the CMS/GC is specified in the rdnPktDQoSCopsCmsIpAddr field. 6 = The CMTS has not received a Keep-Alive message from the CMS/GC within the specified KA timer interval. The IP address of the CMS/GC is specified in the rdnPktDQoSCopsCmsIpAddr field.

rdnPktDQoSCopsCmsIpAddr.name: rdnPktDQoSCopsCmsIpAddr
rdnPktDQoSCopsCmsIpAddr.description: This entry contains the IP address of the CMS/GC associated with the reason code for the rdnPktDQoSCopsTrap.

rdnPktDQoSCopsCmsPortNum.name: rdnPktDQoSCopsCmsPortNum
rdnPktDQoSCopsCmsPortNum.description: This entry contains the TCP port number that the CMS/GC is connected on. This is additional information associated with the reason code for the rdnPktDQoSCopsTrap.

rdnPktDQoSCopsCmsHandleId.name: rdnPktDQoSCopsCmsHandleId
rdnPktDQoSCopsCmsHandleId.description: This entry contains the COPS handle ID associated with the connection to the CMS/GC. This is additional information associated with the reason code for the rdnPktDQoSCopsTrap.

rdnPktDQoSResReqReason.name: rdnPktDQoSResReqReason
rdnPktDQoSResReqReason.description: This entry contains the rdnPktDQoSResReqTrap reason code 1 = The MTA DSA-REQ has requested more resource than it has been authorized. The MTA is identified by the CM's Mac address as specified in the rdnPktDQoSResReqCmMacAddr field. 2 = The MTA DSA-REQ is requesting resource with an unknown Gate ID. 3 = The MTA DSA-REA is requesting resource without including a Gate ID. 4 = The MTA DSC-REQ has requested more resource than it has been authorized. The MTA is identified by the CM's Mac address as specified in the rdnPktDQoSResReqCmMacAddr field. 5 = The MTA DSC-REQ is requesting resource with an unknown Gate ID. 6 = The MTA DSC-REA is requesting resource without including a Gate ID.

rdnPktDQoSCmMacAddr.name: rdnPktDQoSCmMacAddr
rdnPktDQoSCmMacAddr.description: This entry contains the CM's Mac address for the MTA it is associated with. The reason code and this Mac address provide the detailed information for the rdnPktDQoSResReqTrap.

rdnPktDQoSEmergencyReason.name: rdnPktDQoSEmergencyReason
rdnPktDQoSEmergencyReason.description: This entry contains the rdnPktDQoSEmergencyTrap reason code 1 = Emergency Call is rejected due to insufficient bandwidth.

rdnPktDQoSClassName.name: rdnPktDQoSClassName
rdnPktDQoSClassName.description: An ASCII string to identify the Class Name

rdnPktDQoSGateId.name: rdnPktDQoSGateId
rdnPktDQoSGateId.description: This attribute is the identifier for allocated gate. Refer to rdnGateId.

rdnPktDQoSEmergencyPreemptReason.name: rdnPktDQoSEmergencyPreemptReason
rdnPktDQoSEmergencyPreemptReason.description: This entry contains the rdnPktDQoSEmergencyPreempTrap reason code 1 = Emergency call preempted the most recent DQoS call. 2 = Emergency call preempted the oldest DQoS call. 3 = Emergency call preempted a random DQoS call.

rdnPktDQoSCopsTrap.name: rdnPktDQoSCopsTrap
rdnPktDQoSCopsTrap.description: A PacketCable COPS connection status change to the CMS/GC has occurred. The reason code and CMS/GC IP address provide the detailed information regarding this trap.

rdnPktDQoSResReqTrap.name: rdnPktDQoSResReqTrap
rdnPktDQoSResReqTrap.description: A PacketCable MTA resource request problem has occurred (e.g., a problem while processing the DSA-REQ or DSC-REQ was detected). The reason code, the Gate ID, and the CM Mac address, provide detailed information regarding this trap.

rdnPktDQoSEmergencyTrap.name: rdnPktDQoSEmergencyTrap
rdnPktDQoSEmergencyTrap.description: A PacketCable Emergency call is rejected. The reason code, and the CM Mac address, the gate direction, the Channel ID, and the Gate Id provide detailed information regarding this trap.

rdnPktDQoSEmergencyPreemptTrap.name: rdnPktDQoSEmergencyPreemptTrap
rdnPktDQoSEmergencyPreemptTrap.description: A PacketCable Emergency call is preempted successfully. The reason code, and the CM Mac address, the Service Class Name and the Gate Id provide detailed information regarding this trap.

rdnPktESReason.name: rdnPktESReason
rdnPktESReason.description: This entry contains the rdnPktESTrap reason code 1 = Their was no reply from the DF when attempting to send Duplicated Event messages.

rdnPktESDFIpAddr.name: rdnPktESDFIpAddr
rdnPktESDFIpAddr.description: This entry contains the IP address of the DF associated with the reason code for the rdnPktESTrap.

rdnPktESDFPortNum.name: rdnPktESDFPortNum
rdnPktESDFPortNum.description: This entry contains the port number that the DF is connected on. This is additional information associated with the reason code for the rdnPktESTrap.

rdnPktESTrap.name: rdnPktESTrap
rdnPktESTrap.description: A PacketCable ES failure has occurred. The reason code, DF IP address and port provide the detailed information regarding this trap.

rdnPktRKSReason.name: rdnPktRKSReason
rdnPktRKSReason.description: This entry contains the rdnPktRKSTrap reason code 1 = RKS communications failure. Primary and secondary RKS retries exhausted.

rdnPktRKSTransID.name: rdnPktRKSTransID
rdnPktRKSTransID.description: This entry contains the event message Transaction ID. This is additional information associated with the reason code for the rdnPktRKSTrap.

rdnPktRKSIPPrimary.name: rdnPktRKSIPPrimary
rdnPktRKSIPPrimary.description: This entry contains the IP address of the primary RKS. This is additional information associated with the reason code for the rdnPktRKSTrap.

rdnPktRKSPortPrimary.name: rdnPktRKSPortPrimary
rdnPktRKSPortPrimary.description: This entry contains the TCP port number of the primary RKS. This is additional information associated with the reason code for the rdnPktRKSTrap.

rdnPktRKSIPSecondary.name: rdnPktRKSIPSecondary
rdnPktRKSIPSecondary.description: This entry contains the IP address of the secondary RKS. This is additional information associated with the reason code for the rdnPktRKSTrap.

rdnPktRKSPortSecondary.name: rdnPktRKSPortSecondary
rdnPktRKSPortSecondary.description: This entry contains the TCP port number of the secondary RKS. This is additional information associated with the reason code for the rdnPktRKSTrap.

rdnPktRKSVersionID.name: rdnPktRKSVersionID
rdnPktRKSVersionID.description: This entry contains the version ID of the RKS associated with the rdnPktRKSTrap. 1 = Packet Cable 1.0 2 = Packet Cable 1.1 3 = Packet Cable MultiMedia

rdnPktDQoSRKSTrap.name: rdnPktDQoSRKSTrap
rdnPktDQoSRKSTrap.description: There has been a communication failure to both the primary and secondary Record Keeping Servers. The reason code, the ID of the failed Transaction, primary and secondary RKS IP address and port number, and the RKS version type is provided.
